CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 20, 1961, pg. 2 reads: "Henry Ryan Wins - Selma Lloyd, candidate for judge of election in the 11th District of the 13th Ward, and a worker for the Ryan-Washington ticket, is shown with Henry Ryan, who was victorious in his bid for nomination as alderman on the Democratic ticket."
TitMainTitle: Selma Lloyd and Henry Ryan standing in front of brick building with campaign posters for alderman Sarah R. Kirk, Henry R. Smith Jr. for Judge of County Court, and Malvin R. Goode for Councilman, during 1961 primary elections
